Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of the asymptotic behavior of compute-and-forward relay networks, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the use of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) channels, which falls under the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of lattice coding implementation suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the mention of degrees of freedom suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.MM (Multimedia).
